We name rows r1,r2,r3 and columns c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7. By domination,
we are reduced to the following 2 by 3 matrix game:
<br>&nbsp;
<center><table COLS=4 WIDTH="100%" NOSAVE >
<tr>
<td></td>

<td>c3</td>

<td>c4</td>

<td>c5</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>r3</td>

<td>3</td>

<td>0</td>

<td>-2</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>r4</td>

<td>-3</td>

<td>0</td>

<td>2</td>
</tr>
</table></center>

<p>An optimal strategy for the row player is&nbsp; (r3+r4)/2= [0,0,1/2,1/2,0]<sup>T</sup>.
<br>An optimal strategy for the column player is c4=[0,0,0,1,0,0,0].
<br>The value of game is 0.
